just saw Practical Magic.</i>

00:17.285 --> 00:18.684
- Oh, I've been dying to see that.
- (CHUCKLES)

00:18.686 --> 00:20.886
But we're not 12-year-old girls.

00:20.888 --> 00:22.621
- You ready?
- Mm-hmm.

00:22.623 --> 00:24.357
TOBY: When I look at our son,

00:24.359 --> 00:25.791
it just makes me sad.

00:25.793 --> 00:27.326
KATE: I booked us a few days away

00:27.328 --> 00:30.663
with Jack at a retreat
for families with...

00:30.665 --> 00:32.865
blind children.

00:32.867 --> 00:36.035
I thought it sounded like a great thing

00:36.037 --> 00:37.737
to do for our family.

00:37.739 --> 00:40.606
He is reaching for the
light. The doctor said

00:40.608 --> 00:42.326
that he-he might do
that. He might start

00:42.328 --> 00:44.977
<i>to see light and shadows.</i>

00:44.979 --> 00:46.979
<i>YOUNG KATE: Dad?</i>

00:46.981 --> 00:49.349
We have a problem.

00:52.286 --> 00:56.989
Oh, coming in for a landing
on her first big girl bed.

00:56.991 --> 00:59.325
Okay, now...

00:59.327 --> 01:01.160
what is the problem?

01:01.162 --> 01:02.928
I want a Mommy story.

01:02.930 --> 01:04.263
Well, Mommy's asleep, baby.

01:04.265 --> 01:06.065
How 'bout... how 'bout if
Daddy tells you a story?

01:06.067 --> 01:07.099
No.

01:07.101 --> 01:09.769
Okay. Um...

01:09.771 --> 01:13.139
How 'bout you tell me a story?

01:13.141 --> 01:14.640
I don't know how.

01:14.642 --> 01:16.575
That's okay. I can help.

01:16.577 --> 01:18.778
Yeah. Yeah, scoot over.

01:18.780 --> 01:21.313
- Okay. (GRUNTING)
- There you go.

01:21.315 --> 01:23.449
Now,

01:23.451 --> 01:29.121
every good story has a
hero who wants something.

01:29.123 --> 01:32.124
And... he

01:32.126 --> 01:33.692
or she...

01:33.694 --> 01:35.194
- She.
- She.

01:35.196 --> 01:38.831
<i>She</i> has to go on an adventure to get it.

01:38.833 --> 01:41.033
So, I want you to close your eyes, okay?

01:41.035 --> 01:43.431
Close your eyes, and I
want you to picture a hero.

01:43.433 --> 01:45.639
Someone you can <i>really</i> root for.

01:48.276 --> 01:49.675
<i>Who do you see?</i>

01:49.677 --> 01:50.887
<i>KATE: A girl.</i>

01:50.889 --> 01:52.615
A girl. Great.

01:52.617 --> 01:54.647
And where is this girl?

01:54.649 --> 01:56.482
<i>KATE: In a forest.</i>

01:56.484 --> 01:59.685
<i>JACK: She's in a forest? Maybe
it's, like, a magical forest?</i>

01:59.687 --> 02:01.353
<i>KATE: Yeah.</i>

02:01.355 --> 02:02.788
Okay.

02:02.790 --> 02:04.824
Does she meet a prince?

02:04.826 --> 02:07.737
- Yeah.
- Okay. She meets a prince.

02:07.739 --> 02:10.300
But it's not one of those fancy princes

02:10.301 --> 02:11.530
with the poofy sleeves.

02:11.532 --> 02:13.032
Right? He's-he's, like, a...

02:13.034 --> 02:14.533
<i>regular-type prince, right?</i>

02:14.535 --> 02:15.769
<i>KATE: Yeah.</i>

02:17.271 --> 02:19.238
