12:52.588 --> 12:53.954
You were so desperate to show off

12:53.956 --> 12:56.059
to that guy yesterday with
that Neil Diamond stuff,

12:56.061 --> 12:58.203
<i>and I was embarrassed, so I raged out</i>

12:58.205 --> 12:59.706
<i>'cause I'm an idiot.</i>

13:00.466 --> 13:02.467
<i>So, are we okay?</i>

13:06.105 --> 13:07.804
Course we're okay.

13:07.806 --> 13:09.473
How am I gonna stay mad at you?

13:09.475 --> 13:12.477
<i>You're the only good thing in my life.</i>

13:13.322 --> 13:15.322
Um...

13:15.324 --> 13:18.358
I'll see you tomorrow
for your mom's thing.

13:18.360 --> 13:19.893
Okay. I love you.

13:19.895 --> 13:22.162
<i>- I love you, too.
- (DISCONNECT TONE SOUNDS)</i>

13:22.164 --> 13:24.932
(KNOCK ON DOOR)

13:26.001 --> 13:27.968
(SNIFFLES)

13:27.970 --> 13:29.971
(CLEARS THROAT)

13:31.974 --> 13:33.373
Hi.

13:33.375 --> 13:36.276
Hi. Just checking in.

13:36.278 --> 13:37.577
Is everything all right?

13:37.579 --> 13:39.412
Everything's great.

13:39.414 --> 13:41.515
- Yeah?
- Mm-hmm.

13:41.517 --> 13:44.917
You know, I have been
so busy with my new job.

13:44.919 --> 13:48.355
I feel like I've missed out on Marc.

13:48.357 --> 13:50.357
How long have you guys been dating now?

13:50.359 --> 13:52.359
Is it three months?

13:52.361 --> 13:54.361
Yeah, something like that.

13:54.363 --> 13:57.831
Wow. I'd really like to
get to know him better.

13:57.833 --> 13:59.332
Well, yeah.

13:59.334 --> 14:00.867
He's coming to dinner tomorrow night.

14:00.869 --> 14:02.102
Okay.

14:02.104 --> 14:03.804
But, you know, I feel like

14:03.806 --> 14:06.640
it's gonna be crazy with everybody here.

14:06.642 --> 14:10.577
- What if we went to go get coffee before dinner?
- Mm.

14:10.579 --> 14:13.180
- Just the three of us.
- I-I think that's a little excessive.

14:13.182 --> 14:14.616
- (CHUCKLES)
- Oh. Please.

14:14.618 --> 14:16.417
As a gift to me. Your old mom.

14:17.452 --> 14:20.020
Fine. As a gift.

14:20.022 --> 14:22.389
As a gift. Thank you, Bug.

14:22.391 --> 14:24.491
BOY: Whee!

14:24.493 --> 14:26.393
One, two, three.

14:26.395 --> 14:28.495
- Whee!
- (SQUEALS)

14:28.497 --> 14:29.696
You okay, Bug?

14:29.698 --> 14:32.766
Yeah. I'm fine.

14:32.768 --> 14:34.868
What room are we in again?

14:34.870 --> 14:36.870
We are in room...

14:36.872 --> 14:39.940
208 past the saltwater pool.

14:39.942 --> 14:43.310
Says here there is a 1:00
orientation in the courtyard

14:43.312 --> 14:46.346
followed by a braille
workshop in the ballroom.

14:46.348 --> 14:47.914
(GASPS)

14:47.916 --> 14:50.817
And there is nightly
karaoke in the hotel pub.

14:50.819 --> 14:52.786
How wild would it be

14:52.788 --> 14:54.788
- if you and I sang a duet together, huh?
- That...

14:54.790 --> 14:56.957
- Yes, it would be pretty wild. (LAUGHS)
- Come on.

14:56.959 --> 14:58.725
Wait, what is the, um...

14:58.727 --> 15:01.862
What's that Alanis song?
We used to belt it out

15:01.864 --> 15:04.264
every time we heard someone
use the word. What is it?

15:04.266 --> 15:06.199
- Uh, "Ironic"?
- "Ironic". Yes!

15:06.201 --> 15:08.101
- (CHUCKLES)
- "Ironic".

15:08.103 --> 15:09.603
I think of you every
time I hear that song.

15:09.605 --> 15:11.972
- We should sing that song together.
- Really?

15:11.974 --> 15:13.440
- Yeah!
- Mom?

15:13.442 --> 15:15.942
- What?
- Are you on the drugs?

15:15.944 --> 15:18.245
- No, I... Kate.
- (LAUGHS)

15:18.247 --> 15:20.113
No, I'm sorry. I'm just...

15:20.115 --> 15:23.149
I'm excited to be here with you guys.

15:23.151 --> 15:26.152
Well, I appreciate your enthusiasm.

15:26.154 --> 15:29.055
But I am really just, like,
in fact-finding mode, so...

15:29.057 --> 15:31.491
Got it. I'm here for you guys.

15:31.493 --> 15:33.260
Yep.

15:33.262 --> 15:35.896
<i>♪ Everyone was singing ♪</i>

15:35.898 --> 15:39.499
<i>♪ Girl is washed-up ♪</i>

15:39.501 --> 15:42.769
<i>♪ On Redondo Beach ♪</i>

15:42.771 --> 15:46.406
<i>♪ And everyone is so sad ♪</i>

15:46.408 --> 15:49.443
<i>♪ I was looking for you. ♪</i>

15:54.162 --> 15:56.686
Are you sure you told
him the right time?

15:56.688 --> 15:58.222
Yes.

16:01.790 --> 16:04.291
Mom, I know that Kevin and
Randall don't like Marc.

16:04.293 --> 16:05.859
- No.
- And I know

16:05.861 --> 16:08.395
that he can be kind
of intense sometimes,

16:08.397 --> 16:10.997
but, I mean, he's going
through a lot right now, okay?

16:10.999 --> 16:12.582
He's... His parents
are getting a divorce,

16:12.584 --> 16:14.334
and his dad's really hard on him.

16:14.336 --> 16:17.037
Well, I will keep an open mind.

16:17.039 --> 16:18.405
I promise.

16:18.407 --> 16:21.074
Oh, there he is.

16:21.076 --> 16:22.910
KATE: Mm.

16:24.012 --> 16:25.478
- Hey.
- Sorry I'm late.

16:25.480 --> 16:26.646
My car's a piece of crap.

16:26.648 --> 16:28.215
Oh, no. The battery again?

16:29.084 --> 16:30.917
It's good to see you, Marc.

16:30.919 --> 16:33.074
- (MARC SIGHS)
- Sorry about your car.

16:33.076 --> 16:35.355
Thanks. Yeah, it sucks.

16:35.357 --> 16:36.457
Hello?

16:37.459 --> 16:39.293
Hey. (WHISTLES)

16:42.097 --> 16:43.898
(EXHALES)

16:45.667 --> 16:47.033
Uh...

16:47.035 --> 16:48.969
God, I'm sorry.

16:48.971 --> 16:50.804
I just charged in here
like a bat out of hell.

16:50.806 --> 16:52.272
- I'm Meat Loaf.
- Like Meat Loaf.

16:52.274 --> 16:53.540
(CHUCKLES)

16:53.542 --> 16:55.575
(LAUGHS)

16:55.577 --> 16:58.078
Aw. You guys must really love

16:58.080 --> 16:59.980
working at the record
store together, huh?

16:59.982 --> 17:02.482
- Yeah.
- MARC: Yeah. Yeah, I liked it.

17:02.484 --> 17:05.185
Yeah. I feel like I've
kind of outgrown it, though.

17:06.722 --> 17:10.156
Um... Just Terry, our, um...

17:10.157 --> 17:12.070
He's our manager. He's
just so incompetent.

17:12.073 --> 17:13.396
He's getting on me all the time

17:13.397 --> 17:14.653
about taking too many smoke breaks.

17:14.655 --> 17:16.061
Like, it's total BS, so,

17:16.064 --> 17:18.766
you know, I just quit.

17:19.835 --> 17:21.634
When did you quit?

17:21.636 --> 17:23.570
This morning.

17:28.710 --> 17:31.778
Do you know, um, the singer Patti Smith?

17:31.780 --> 17:33.113
Mm-hmm.

17:33.115 --> 17:35.915
Um, 'cause he got me

17:35.917 --> 17:37.350
this really awesome book, <i>Babel.</i>

17:37.352 --> 17:38.685
It's really inspiring.

17:38.687 --> 17:40.120
- Yeah.
- So sweet.

17:40.122 --> 17:41.688
MARC: Mm.

17:41.690 --> 17:44.124
Yeah. You know, Kate and
I are gonna actually write

17:44.126 --> 17:45.792
some songs together.

17:45.794 --> 17:49.029
Yeah, your daughter has
a really amazing voice.

17:49.031 --> 17:50.330
It's very sweet,

17:50.332 --> 17:53.199
but also, it's very soulful.

17:53.201 --> 17:54.734
REBECCA: Mm-hmm.

17:54.736 --> 17:56.603
Well, I agree with you there.

17:56.605 --> 17:58.938
I can't wait to hear these songs, Kate.

17:58.940 --> 18:00.440
- (CHUCKLES) Yeah.
- Yeah.

18:00.442 --> 18:02.142
We just got to get out of
Pittsburgh to write them.

18:02.144 --> 18:03.810
- (KATE CHUCKLES)
- Oh, ooh!

18:03.812 --> 18:05.345
Hey, we should go to that cabin

18:05.347 --> 18:07.447
that you're always talking about.

18:07.449 --> 18:08.581
Our family cabin?

18:08.583 --> 18:09.682
- MARC: Yeah.
- KATE: Yeah.

18:09.684 --> 18:12.465
Oh. We haven't even opened
it up for the season.

18:12.467 --> 18:14.220
I totally forgot.

18:14.222 --> 18:15.855
- We can open it.
- (MARC CHUCKLES)

18:15.857 --> 18:17.891
I love it. Our own Shangri-la.

18:17.893 --> 18:19.993
(IMITATING JOHN LENNON):
Like Yoko and John.

18:19.995 --> 18:21.995
(CHUCKLES)

18:21.997 --> 18:24.665
That is an idea.

18:26.868 --> 18:29.603
(REBECCA AND MARC CHUCKLE)

18:31.770 --> 18:34.291
So, the little girl
walks through the flowers.

18:34.903 --> 18:38.571
What does she... What do
you think she sees next, huh?

18:38.573 --> 18:39.939
Water.

18:39.941 --> 18:42.141
Great idea.

18:42.143 --> 18:45.345
<i>The little girl and the
prince came upon a dark cave</i>

18:45.347 --> 18:47.982
<i>dripping with water.</i>

18:49.384 --> 18:50.851
♪♪

19:05.133 --> 19:07.134
(INDISTINCT CHATTER)

19:12.240 --> 19:14.240
<i>WOMAN: Being the parent of a child</i>

19:14.242 --> 19:16.976
with a disability can
sometimes feel overwhelming,

19:16.978 --> 19:19.379
but there are so many tools out there

19:19.381 --> 19:22.382
that can make life easier
for you and your family.

19:22.384 --> 19:24.150
By finding

19:24.152 --> 19:26.586
TV programs and films
with audio description,

19:26.588 --> 19:29.722
your child can hear key visual elements

19:29.724 --> 19:31.759
so that they can share
in the full experience.

19:33.128 --> 19:34.727
- (CLICKING)
- Basically, he makes

19:34.729 --> 19:36.729
these clicking noises,
kind of like a dolphin.

19:36.731 --> 19:38.731
And the clicks bounce off of stuff,

19:38.733 --> 19:39.933
and he somehow figures out where he is

19:39.935 --> 19:41.467
so he doesn't crash into anything.

19:41.469 --> 19:42.635
- REBECCA: Oh!
- It's not

19:42.637 --> 19:44.637
that common, but Zak
wanted to give it a try.

19:44.639 --> 19:46.005
At first, I was afraid that using a cane

19:46.007 --> 19:47.073
would stigmatize me.

19:47.075 --> 19:48.775
But it's actually very empowering

19:48.777 --> 19:50.209
and gives me a lot of independence.

19:50.211 --> 19:51.811
- When you walk...<i>
- MAN: For those of you</i>

19:51.813 --> 19:55.782
brand-new to this, braille
is a six-dot system.

19:55.784 --> 19:57.784
First note is "C".

19:57.786 --> 19:59.419
Can you find "C" on the keyboard?

19:59.421 --> 20:00.920
("C" PLAYS)

20:00.922 --> 20:02.322
Good work.

20:02.324 --> 20:03.890
It's that easy.

20:03.892 --> 20:06.360
Who can tell me what the second note is?

20:08.863 --> 20:11.564
Hey. Marc and I are gonna
leave, like, really early

20:11.566 --> 20:12.932
in the morning to beat traffic,

20:12.934 --> 20:14.534
so are the keys to the cabin

20:14.536 --> 20:16.836
still in the hidey place
near the front steps?

20:16.838 --> 20:19.272
Um, sweetheart,

20:19.274 --> 20:21.074
I don't... I don't know
if I feel comfortable

20:21.076 --> 20:22.508
with you guys going up there alone.

20:22.510 --> 20:23.977
Why not?

20:23.979 --> 20:26.713
I just... I don't
think it's a good idea.

20:26.715 --> 20:28.715
What? That is so unfair.

20:28.717 --> 20:31.651
Randall's off with Beth doing
God knows what every night,

20:31.653 --> 20:33.653
and-and Kevin's literally married.

20:33.655 --> 20:36.022
- It's different.
- Why?

20:36.024 --> 20:38.024
- 'Cause I'm a girl?
- No.

20:38.026 --> 20:39.425
Oh.

20:39.427 --> 20:41.594
- Because you don't like Marc.
- Honey,

20:41.596 --> 20:43.596
I don't even really know Marc.

20:43.598 --> 20:46.265
Great. Great. You hate him, too.

20:46.267 --> 20:49.168
No. I don't hate him, Kate.

20:49.170 --> 20:51.304
I even understand what
you like about him.

20:51.306 --> 20:53.907
- I mean, he's passionate, and he's creative and...
- Just stop.

20:55.110 --> 20:57.510
You know what?

20:57.512 --> 21:00.513
After Dad...

21:00.515 --> 21:04.818
I genuinely thought I
would never be happy again.

21:05.820 --> 21:07.353
I understand.

21:07.355 --> 21:08.888
No, you don't.

21:08.890 --> 21:10.890
You don't, Mom. Look at you.

21:10.892 --> 21:13.567
You've had boys falling
all over you for, what,

21:13.569 --> 21:15.637
your entire life?

21:17.899 --> 21:20.066
Marc loves me,

21:20.068 --> 21:24.270
and he's the first guy to
ever be interested in me.

21:24.272 --> 21:27.974
The first person to ever
even look at me that way.

21:27.976 --> 21:30.009
I understand.

21:30.011 --> 21:32.779
You don't!

21:32.781 --> 21:34.814
I don't need you to like him.

21:34.816 --> 21:36.716
<i>I</i> like him.

21:36.718 --> 21:39.252
We're not going to the cabin
tomorrow. We're going now.

21:39.254 --> 21:41.509
So, sorry if that ruins
your birthday dinner,

21:41.511 --> 21:44.279
but I'm sure Miguel will be
around to pick up the pieces.

21:44.281 --> 21:45.992
Whoa.

21:45.994 --> 21:47.882
That is not fair.

21:47.884 --> 21:50.486
Yeah, neither was this.

21:52.905 --> 21:54.994
<i>KATE: Yeah, it was amazing!</i>

21:54.996 --> 21:57.170
He was making these,
like, clicking noises, and

21:57.172 --> 21:59.505
so he could just ride his
bike everywhere. It was...

21:59.507 --> 22:02.022
Your mind would have been blown.

22:02.024 --> 22:03.142
<i>GREGORY: That is so cool.</i>

22:03.144 --> 22:04.811
<i>Jack will be the same way.</i>

22:04.813 --> 22:06.212
I've seen the look of wild abandon

22:06.214 --> 22:08.214
on his face whenever we power walk.

22:08.216 --> 22:09.816
(LAUGHS)

22:09.818 --> 22:12.985
Uh, hey, I'm gonna call it, but, um...

22:12.987 --> 22:15.889
You, too. Bye.

22:17.092 --> 22:20.226
How is Toby doing?

22:20.228 --> 22:22.563
He's good. He's just busy.

22:24.032 --> 22:27.066
Sweetheart, um,

22:27.068 --> 22:29.402
there's something I really
wanted to talk to you about.

22:29.404 --> 22:31.938
Okay, that wasn't Toby on the phone.

22:31.940 --> 22:33.196
What?

22:33.198 --> 22:35.141
It was Gregory, my neighbor,
you know, with the beard,

22:35.143 --> 22:36.542
who had the stroke.

22:36.544 --> 22:39.179
- Oh.
- Yeah.

22:42.283 --> 22:44.888
Toby didn't have a work thing.

22:44.890 --> 22:49.816
He has been struggling
with Jack's blindness.

22:49.818 --> 22:53.359
And he said that every
time that he looks at Jack,

22:53.361 --> 22:54.794
it just makes him sad.

22:54.796 --> 22:56.262
Mm.

22:56.264 --> 22:59.198
So... That's a direct quote.

22:59.200 --> 23:01.667
Yeah.

23:01.669 --> 23:04.303
He is struggling.

23:04.305 --> 23:06.507
And I'm not?

23:08.643 --> 23:11.644
He is supposed to be
running around, right,

23:11.646 --> 23:13.679
riding bikes and
taking Jack to the pool.

23:13.681 --> 23:15.965
Well, you can take him to the pool, too.

23:15.967 --> 23:19.218
Mom, I have spent half the
day having a panic attack

23:19.220 --> 23:21.854
about wearing a bathing
suit in public without him.

23:21.856 --> 23:23.990
And I-I...

23:23.992 --> 23:26.893
Someday, Jack's gonna
want to ride a bike,

23:26.895 --> 23:29.562
and I don't know if I'm gonna
be able to do that with him.

23:29.564 --> 23:33.866
And I don't know if-if
Toby is going to want to,

23:33.868 --> 23:37.069
if he's gonna be here. I don't...

23:37.071 --> 23:39.639
I don't know.

23:39.641 --> 23:41.675
Wha...

23:42.811 --> 23:45.311
(PATS BED) Come on, get up.

23:45.313 --> 23:46.435
What?

23:46.437 --> 23:47.947
We're gonna go swimming. Right now.

23:47.949 --> 23:49.148
- What?
- Right now!

23:49.150 --> 23:50.183
- No.
- Where's your bathing suit?

23:50.185 --> 23:51.384
- Mom...
- We are. Uh-huh.

23:51.386 --> 23:52.718
Okay, I found it.

23:52.720 --> 23:53.776
Let's go, let's go.

23:53.778 --> 23:54.854
It's, like... It's 9:00.

23:54.856 --> 23:55.988
The pool is closed anyway.

23:55.990 --> 23:57.056
I don't care.

23:57.058 --> 23:58.491
Come on!

23:58.493 --> 23:59.892
I'm not going swimming.

23:59.894 --> 24:01.394
Kate, come on.

24:01.396 --> 24:04.764
You're fat, I'm ancient. We're gorgeous.

24:04.766 --> 24:07.233
Let's go swimming. Put
on your suit, come on.

24:07.235 --> 24:08.801
I'm gonna get on mine. Come on.

24:08.803 --> 24:09.970
Let's go.

24:12.185 --> 24:14.186
♪♪

24:36.298 --> 24:38.166
(CHUCKLES SOFTLY)

24:42.071 --> 24:45.606
You know I used to have to
drag you out of the pool.

24:45.608 --> 24:49.205
You would hold up your...
your wrinkly little hand

24:49.207 --> 24:52.312
- and say, "Mom, look. They're like raisins".
- (KATE CHUCKLES)

24:52.314 --> 24:53.981
Remember that?

24:53.983 --> 24:56.516
Yeah.

24:56.518 --> 24:58.843
It's ironic.

24:58.845 --> 25:01.102
The only place I feel
weightless is the place

25:01.104 --> 25:03.338
I've avoided my entire life.

25:05.708 --> 25:07.642
You're here, Bug.

25:07.644 --> 25:09.644
Let the weight go.

25:09.646 --> 25:12.514
Take everything off your shoulders

25:12.516 --> 25:14.582
and give it to me; I can take it.

25:14.584 --> 25:18.086
That's what I'm here for.

25:21.157 --> 25:23.058
♪♪

25:31.034 --> 25:33.467
You know why I call you Bug?

25:33.469 --> 25:37.872
Yeah, 'cause I was a weird
kid who was obsessed with bugs.

25:37.874 --> 25:40.975
- (BOTH LAUGH)
- Obsessed is an understatement.

25:40.977 --> 25:43.477
You loved everything that could fly.

25:43.479 --> 25:45.246
Everything. Oh, gosh.

25:45.248 --> 25:47.882
Butterflies and ladybugs

25:47.884 --> 25:50.885
and bumblebees.

25:50.887 --> 25:54.555
But your favorite were lightning bugs.

25:54.557 --> 25:57.049
Or, as you called
them, "light bulb bugs".

25:57.051 --> 25:58.185
(BOTH CHUCKLE)

26:00.463 --> 26:03.464
Oh, I can see it as clear as day.

26:03.466 --> 26:06.667
<i>You in our front yard,</i>

26:06.669 --> 26:09.169
<i>your eyes as big as saucers,</i>

26:09.171 --> 26:12.740
<i>watching the lightning bugs
as they flickered on and off.</i>

26:12.742 --> 26:16.343
You were so gentle.

26:16.345 --> 26:18.445
<i>You used to gently
cup one in your hands,</i>

26:18.447 --> 26:20.981
<i>and you'd watch it</i>

26:20.983 --> 26:22.940
as it lit up.

26:22.942 --> 26:25.252
And then you would
whisper in the sweetest

26:25.254 --> 26:26.353
<i>little voice...</i>

26:26.355 --> 26:27.955
Go find your way home.

26:27.957 --> 26:30.090
"Go find your way home".

26:30.092 --> 26:31.692
You'd open up

26:31.694 --> 26:33.461
<i>your little hand and let it fly away.</i>

26:38.334 --> 26:41.735
My sensitive little Bug.

26:41.737 --> 26:44.738
Always, always empathizing

26:44.740 --> 26:48.743
with everyone and everything.

26:50.407 --> 26:51.930
But just because you're sensitive

26:51.932 --> 26:53.599
doesn't mean you're not strong.

26:55.551 --> 26:59.254
I don't... I don't
feel strong right now.

27:00.823 --> 27:04.158
I have known you for
all of your 39 years,

27:04.160 --> 27:07.642
and you are much stronger than
anyone gives you credit for,

27:07.644 --> 27:08.695
including yourself.

27:08.697 --> 27:11.965
Yeah, you've been dealt
a bit of a curveball.

27:11.967 --> 27:16.503
Toby's not bouncing back as
quickly as you would like.

27:16.505 --> 27:19.006
But you need to not
be afraid to tell him

27:19.008 --> 27:20.842
that he needs to step it up.

27:22.511 --> 27:24.578
But what if he doesn't, ever?

27:24.580 --> 27:27.815
Well, then, you are perfectly capable

27:27.817 --> 27:31.319
of raising Jack
beautifully all on your own.

27:33.722 --> 27:37.325
But I... I believe in Toby.

27:39.962 --> 27:42.463
He'll find his way home.

27:47.703 --> 27:49.704
Okay...

27:52.675 --> 27:55.176
Now I need to get
something off my shoulders.

27:56.412 --> 27:58.278
Is everything okay?

27:58.280 --> 28:01.582
Yeah, yeah, yeah.
Let's-let's dry off first.

28:01.584 --> 28:04.218
Okay.

28:04.220 --> 28:06.887
<i>JACK: The little girl
knew she had to be brave.</i>

28:06.889 --> 28:10.624
<i>So, finally, she
gathered all her courage</i>

28:10.626 --> 28:12.993
<i>- and took one big step...
- YOUNG KATE: Dad!</i>

28:12.995 --> 28:14.695
This is <i>my</i> story.

28:14.697 --> 28:17.397
Okay, yeah, you're right.
You're right, it is your story.

28:17.399 --> 28:19.299
So you-you go ahead.

28:19.301 --> 28:21.368
<i>YOUNG KATE: And then the...</i>

28:21.370 --> 28:24.371
<i>And then the prince disappears.</i>

28:24.373 --> 28:28.375
Wow. (CHUCKLES)

28:28.377 --> 28:30.344
That is a great twist.

28:30.346 --> 28:32.546
♪♪

28:32.548 --> 28:34.615
<i>TEENAGE KATE: Here we go.</i>

28:34.617 --> 28:36.617
<i>KATE and MARC (SINGING
ALONG): ♪ And you can see ♪</i>

28:36.619 --> 28:41.154
<i>♪ The daisies in her footsteps ♪</i>

28:41.156 --> 28:42.789
<i>♪ Oh, oh, oh ♪</i>

28:42.791 --> 28:44.858
<i>♪ Dandelions, dandelions ♪</i>

28:44.860 --> 28:46.260
<i>♪ Butterflies ♪</i>

28:46.262 --> 28:48.996
<i>♪ I wanna be Kate ♪</i>

28:48.998 --> 28:50.697
<i>♪ Kate ♪</i>

28:50.699 --> 28:51.865
<i>♪ Bom, bom, Kate ♪</i>

28:51.867 --> 28:53.734
<i>♪ Bom, bom, bom, bom, bom, Kate ♪</i>

28:53.736 --> 28:55.068
<i>♪ Unh, Kate, Kate ♪</i>

28:55.070 --> 28:57.137
<i>♪ Every day she wears the same thing ♪</i>

28:57.139 --> 28:58.872
- <i>♪ Every day she smokes pot ♪</i>
- Dang.

28:58.874 --> 29:00.774
- <i>♪ She's everything I want... ♪</i>
- You know,

29:00.776 --> 29:02.276
I'm kind of bummed you quit.

29:02.278 --> 29:03.906
I mean, I know Terry's lame and all,

29:03.908 --> 29:05.580
but I'm gonna miss you there.

29:07.449 --> 29:10.585
Well, maybe you should quit, too.

29:13.122 --> 29:15.822
Yeah, well... well, honestly,
I need the money right now.

29:15.824 --> 29:19.626
And, I mean, it's...
it's a pretty decent job.

29:19.628 --> 29:22.362
As far as, like, dumb jobs go.

29:22.364 --> 29:24.464
Uh-huh. I mean, I guess.

29:24.466 --> 29:27.000
But, uh, I'm gonna make music

29:27.002 --> 29:29.536
instead of just talking about it.

29:29.538 --> 29:31.004
Yeah, I know.

29:31.006 --> 29:34.807
<i>♪ Down by the Rosemary and Cameron ♪</i>

29:34.809 --> 29:37.945
<i>♪ She hands out the</i> Bhagavad Gita ♪

29:39.014 --> 29:42.716
<i>♪ I see her around
every couple days... ♪</i>

29:42.718 --> 29:44.451
So just to be clear,
you're not gonna quit.

29:44.453 --> 29:46.253
<i>♪ So that I can say ♪</i>

29:46.255 --> 29:47.988
<i>♪ Hey, Kate... ♪</i>

29:47.990 --> 29:49.156
Of course not.

29:49.158 --> 29:51.024
- No.
- (MUSIC TURNS UP)

29:51.541 --> 29:52.675
Hmm.

29:54.797 --> 29:57.465
That's great support, Kate.

30:01.070 --> 30:02.836
Marc, can you slow down?

30:02.838 --> 30:04.338
Really, like, after the
way Terry treated me?

30:04.340 --> 30:06.707
And I got you that job!
Do you remember that?

30:06.709 --> 30:07.908
- No, I know, but can you slow down?
- No, no, no.

30:07.910 --> 30:11.580
- (MARC SPEAKS INDISTINCTLY)
- KATE: Slow down!

30:11.582 --> 30:14.617
Marc, please, please slow down.

30:15.918 --> 30:17.718
You're going too fast. Please!

30:21.290 --> 30:23.290
Marc, stop the car now!

30:24.827 --> 30:26.260
(GASPS)

30:27.696 --> 30:29.696
Thank you.

30:29.698 --> 30:31.965
<i>♪ Oh, oh ♪</i>

30:31.967 --> 30:35.802
Babe... let's just get some air.

30:35.804 --> 30:37.004
Okay?

30:37.006 --> 30:38.205
Come on.

30:38.207 --> 30:42.342
<i>♪ Kate, Kate. ♪</i>

30:42.344 --> 30:44.011
Babe, come on...

30:44.013 --> 30:45.735
You know, I can't even
look at your fat face!

30:45.737 --> 30:46.737
Marc...

30:47.616 --> 30:49.083
Marc!

30:59.084 --> 31:01.954
Mom, you're starting to
freak me out; what's going on?

31:01.956 --> 31:03.623
Okay, um...

31:05.492 --> 31:08.393
I've been having some
memory issues lately.

31:08.395 --> 31:11.997
Forgetting my phone, forgetting words.

31:11.999 --> 31:14.633
Small things. Little things.

31:14.635 --> 31:17.603
But Randall noticed that
something was off with me

31:17.605 --> 31:21.173
around Thanksgiving, and I
went to have some tests done.

31:21.175 --> 31:23.342
- Oh, my God, Mom...
- No, no, hold on.

31:23.344 --> 31:25.477
Nothing is certain,

31:25.479 --> 31:29.448
but they did diagnose
me with something called

31:29.450 --> 31:32.719
mild cognitive impairment.

31:32.721 --> 31:35.678
Which could eventually lead

31:35.680 --> 31:39.750
to dementia or Alzheimer's.

31:51.563 --> 31:52.995
(EXHALES SHARPLY)

31:52.997 --> 31:55.865
How did I not notice anything?

31:55.867 --> 31:58.234
Because I didn't want
you to notice anything.

31:58.236 --> 32:00.436
I'm fine. I'm fine.

32:00.438 --> 32:02.572
We don't even know
where this may lead yet.

32:02.574 --> 32:05.274
And if anything, I...

32:05.276 --> 32:08.911
The diagnosis has made
me feel more powerful.

32:08.913 --> 32:11.080
And more fun.

32:11.082 --> 32:13.082
You have been more fun.

32:13.084 --> 32:15.084
- Right?
- (CHUCKLES)

32:15.086 --> 32:18.554
'Cause I'm not sweating the small stuff.

32:18.556 --> 32:22.391
Hey. I don't know how much longer I have

32:22.393 --> 32:27.096
before things might get worse,
so... I'm-I'm done being sad,

32:27.098 --> 32:29.732
and I'm done feeling worried.

32:29.734 --> 32:31.735
I feel...

32:35.373 --> 32:37.374
I feel okay.

32:45.750 --> 32:47.317
Okay.

32:48.353 --> 32:49.586
Yeah.

32:50.989 --> 32:54.624
I am strong.

32:54.626 --> 32:57.560
You made me strong.

32:57.562 --> 32:59.563
(CRYING SOFTLY)

33:05.904 --> 33:07.104
(SNIFFLES)

33:12.443 --> 33:15.345
(GRUNTS) Is Jack still asleep?

33:17.515 --> 33:18.948
- Uh...
- Oh, yeah. He's out.

33:18.950 --> 33:20.750
(LAUGHS)

33:20.752 --> 33:22.151
Let's get dressed.

33:22.153 --> 33:23.720
I have an idea.

33:26.291 --> 33:32.161
<i>♪ Hey, yeah, ah, ah, ah, yeah ♪</i>

33:32.163 --> 33:34.164
(LAUGHS)

33:36.000 --> 33:41.270
<i>♪ An old man turned 98 ♪</i>

33:41.272 --> 33:43.639
<i>♪ He won the lottery ♪</i>

33:43.641 --> 33:47.043
<i>♪ And died the next day ♪</i>

33:47.045 --> 33:52.648
<i>♪ It's a black fly in your Chardonnay ♪</i>

33:52.650 --> 33:57.787
<i>♪ It's a death row pardon
two minutes too late ♪</i>

33:57.789 --> 33:59.855
<i>♪ And isn't it ironic ♪</i>

33:59.857 --> 34:03.226
- <i>♪ Don't you think? ♪</i>
- (LAUGHS)

34:03.228 --> 34:06.362
<i>♪ It's like rain ♪</i>

34:06.364 --> 34:08.998
<i>♪ On your wedding day ♪</i>

34:09.000 --> 34:12.568
<i>♪ It's a free ride ♪</i>

34:12.570 --> 34:14.603
<i>♪ When you've already paid ♪</i>

34:14.606 --> 34:17.373
<i>♪ It's the good advice... ♪</i>

34:17.375 --> 34:19.243
♪♪

34:29.786 --> 34:31.521
(PANTING)

34:37.027 --> 34:39.027
(LINE RINGING)

34:39.030 --> 34:41.864
<i>- REBECCA (OVER PHONE): Hello?
- Hi, Mom.</i>

34:41.866 --> 34:44.166
Hi, Kate.

34:44.168 --> 34:46.768
<i>You okay? Did you guys
make it up to the cabin?</i>

34:46.771 --> 34:48.771
Um, no, not yet.

34:48.773 --> 34:51.474
We, uh, we decided to
stop at a gas station.

34:51.476 --> 34:53.109
But, um,

34:53.110 --> 34:56.246
I'm sorry for what I said earlier.

34:57.282 --> 34:58.581
<i>I'm really sorry</i>

34:58.583 --> 35:00.416
I'm missing your birthday.

35:00.418 --> 35:02.184
<i>It's fine, Bug.</i>

35:02.186 --> 35:04.553
I'm sorry, too.

35:04.555 --> 35:06.188
You sound kind of upset.

35:06.190 --> 35:09.325
<i>Is everything all right?</i>

35:09.327 --> 35:12.329
No. Mom...

35:15.166 --> 35:17.533
<i>Bug?</i>

35:17.535 --> 35:19.935
Kate? Are you okay?

35:19.937 --> 35:22.471
Talk to me.

35:22.473 --> 35:23.639
(WHISPERS): I'm sorry.

35:23.641 --> 35:25.875
Uh... um...

35:25.877 --> 35:27.877
<i>Everything's fine.</i>

35:27.879 --> 35:29.478
<i>I-I'm sorry, Mom.</i>

35:29.480 --> 35:30.746
I love you, okay? Bye.

35:30.748 --> 35:32.315
<i>Okay... I love you, too...</i>

35:32.317 --> 35:34.318
- Well...
- (DIAL TONE SOUNDS)

35:41.526 --> 35:43.326
Dad!

35:43.328 --> 35:44.727
(WHISPERS): You fell asleep.

35:44.729 --> 35:47.764
Yeah. Yeah.

35:55.807 --> 35:58.407
(WHISPERS): Sorry.

35:58.409 --> 36:00.409
I'm sorry.

36:00.411 --> 36:03.245
Don't you want to know what she wants?

36:03.247 --> 36:04.980
Yeah.

36:04.982 --> 36:07.818
Yeah, why don't, why don't
you tell me what she wants?

36:25.670 --> 36:27.269
(LAUGHS)

36:27.271 --> 36:29.105
My sweet little bug.

36:29.107 --> 36:31.742
- (LAUGHS)
- My sweet little bug.

36:37.045 --> 36:39.813
(EXHALES)

36:39.815 --> 36:42.216
What are you gonna say to Toby?

36:44.108 --> 36:46.609
I'm just gonna be very clear

36:46.611 --> 36:48.444
about what my family needs from him.

36:48.446 --> 36:51.647
And about what I need from him.

36:51.649 --> 36:55.651
Well, just so you know, you
always have a safety net.

36:55.653 --> 36:59.789
I'm always available if you need
a... a <i>Friends</i> marathon.

37:00.758 --> 37:02.158
Whatever.

37:02.160 --> 37:03.793
(LAUGHS)

37:03.795 --> 37:05.528
Am I slowly becoming one of those women

37:05.530 --> 37:08.365
- whose best friend is their mom?
- (LAUGHS)

37:11.002 --> 37:14.236
Stranger things have happened.

37:14.238 --> 37:16.238
(QUIETLY): Yeah.

37:16.240 --> 37:18.074
Will you call me tonight?

37:18.076 --> 37:20.076
- Yeah, I will.
- Okay.

37:20.078 --> 37:23.145
(WHISPERS): Bye, Jack.

37:23.147 --> 37:24.914
Hey, Mom?

37:24.916 --> 37:26.116
Hmm?

37:29.821 --> 37:32.689
Go do what you got to do.

37:34.158 --> 37:36.159
Okay.

37:46.838 --> 37:48.839
(CAR DOOR CLOSES)

37:53.377 --> 37:57.079
- Hey.
- Hey.

37:57.081 --> 37:59.715
Um, we just got home.

37:59.717 --> 38:03.820
Madison left a note. She
walked Audio and Jack is asleep.

38:04.956 --> 38:09.825
Yeah. Yeah, I just, I
just looked in on him.

38:09.827 --> 38:12.262
- How was it?
- It was incredible.

38:14.132 --> 38:16.133
And you would have loved it.

38:19.170 --> 38:21.171
Yeah.

38:23.241 --> 38:25.242
Toby.

38:26.911 --> 38:30.212
Can you, can you do this?

38:30.214 --> 38:33.993
I mean, can you, can you be
the man that I need you to be?

38:33.995 --> 38:37.196
Can you be the father
that Jack needs you to be?

38:37.198 --> 38:39.867
I want to.

38:42.404 --> 38:44.838
(PHONE BUZZING)

38:47.242 --> 38:49.242
It's my brother.

38:49.244 --> 38:51.944
(CLEARS THROAT)

38:51.946 --> 38:55.281
Hey, Kev. Um... Um, what's up?

38:55.283 --> 38:57.650
You know, now is not really a good time.

38:57.652 --> 38:59.952
- Um...<i>
- KEVIN (OVER PHONE): Why? What's the matter?</i>

38:59.954 --> 39:03.556
Uh, well, I'm about two seconds away

39:03.558 --> 39:06.326
from my marriage completely imploding.

39:08.029 --> 39:09.797
Oh, Kate, I'm so sorry.

39:15.290 --> 39:17.013
Listen, I got Randall on the other line.

39:17.015 --> 39:19.972
<i>Life's kind of sucking
for him, too, right now.</i>

39:19.974 --> 39:21.974
<i>You mind if I patch him through?</i>

39:21.976 --> 39:23.610
- Yeah.<i>
- Yeah.</i>

39:25.569 --> 39:27.892
<i>Hey, Randall, I got Kate.</i>

39:27.894 --> 39:30.451
<i>She's kind of in a bad
way, too, actually.</i>

39:30.453 --> 39:32.285
Sad three?

39:32.287 --> 39:34.488
Sad three.

39:36.044 --> 39:37.901
<i>RANDALL: Hey, Kate, Kev and I</i>

39:37.903 --> 39:40.626
were just talking about
going out to the cabin.

39:40.628 --> 39:42.629
<i>You want to join us?</i>

39:46.534 --> 39:48.535
(FOOTSTEPS APPROACHING)

39:51.406 --> 39:54.217
Toby, I don't need you to just want

39:54.219 --> 39:57.922
to be a good father to Jack,
I need you to just do it.

39:59.914 --> 40:02.915
I'm gonna take Jack to the cabin
this weekend with my brothers.

40:02.917 --> 40:05.452
'Cause I just need some space right now.

40:07.188 --> 40:09.289
Let me take care of Jack this weekend.

40:11.559 --> 40:13.392
Well, I don't think that's a good idea.

40:13.394 --> 40:16.896
Uh, actually, I...
yeah... I-I think it is.

40:16.898 --> 40:19.865
You go to the cabin, and
leave Jack here with me.

40:19.867 --> 40:21.067
I'll take care of him.

40:23.271 --> 40:27.207
I need to spend time with my son.

40:29.143 --> 40:31.144
Kate, please.

40:33.314 --> 40:34.548
Okay.

40:35.583 --> 40:37.618
(QUIETLY): Okay.

40:42.857 --> 40:44.858
♪♪

40:48.229 --> 40:50.963
<i>REBECCA: I'm worried about Kate.</i>

40:50.965 --> 40:53.900
I think she's in trouble, Kev.

40:53.902 --> 40:55.334
We have to go get her.

40:55.336 --> 40:57.247
Uh, okay. Go-go get your stuff together.

40:57.249 --> 40:58.605
And I'll call Randall right now.

40:58.607 --> 41:00.608
Okay.

41:08.783 --> 41:10.784
(SPEAKING INDISTINCTLY)

41:13.821 --> 41:16.188
<i>KEVIN: Mom cancelled
her birthday dinner.</i>

41:16.190 --> 41:18.858
- <i>RANDALL: Wait, why?</i>
- KEVIN: Something's wrong with Kate. Um,

41:18.860 --> 41:20.359
I'll explain in the car.
Just be ready in 20.

41:20.361 --> 41:21.460
We're coming to pick you up.

41:21.462 --> 41:22.662
<i>- All right?
- O-Okay.</i>

41:22.664 --> 41:24.131
I-I'll be downstairs.

41:25.266 --> 41:29.169
Uh, is everything okay?

41:35.276 --> 41:38.545
Snug as a bug in a rug.

41:47.989 --> 41:51.057
- (GRUNTS SOFTLY)
- (EXHALES)

41:51.059 --> 41:52.825
How'd it go? How'd they do?

41:52.827 --> 41:55.461
Oh. Piece of cake.

41:55.463 --> 41:58.130
Yeah. Everybody's asleep.

41:58.132 --> 42:00.433
I told you, I got it.

42:00.435 --> 42:02.435
- Mm. My hero.
- (CHUCKLES)

42:02.437 --> 42:05.037
Yeah.

42:05.039 --> 42:06.773
I just put them to bed one night.

42:08.409 --> 42:10.410
<i>You're the real hero.</i>

